### OpenClaw Models Fallbacks

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/cli/models.md

Manages fallback models that are used when the primary model is unavailable.

```APIDOC
## Fallbacks Management

### Description
Commands for managing fallback models. These are used sequentially if the primary or preceding fallback model fails.

### Method
Various (list, add, remove)

### Endpoint
/openclaw/models/fallbacks

### Commands
- `openclaw models fallbacks list`: Lists all configured fallback models in order.
- `openclaw models fallbacks add <model_identifier>`: Adds a model to the end of the fallback list.
- `openclaw models fallbacks remove <model_identifier>`: Removes a model from the fallback list.

### Request Example (List Fallbacks)
```bash
openclaw models fallbacks list
```

### Response Example (List Fallbacks)
```json
{
  "fallbacks": [
    "anthropic/claude-3-sonnet",
    "google/gemini-1.5-pro-latest"
  ]
}
```
```

--------------------------------

### Configure OpenClaw Agent with Primary and Fallback Ollama Models

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/providers/ollama.md

Sets a primary Ollama model and a fallback model for agent operations. This ensures that if the primary model is unavailable, the agent can use the fallback.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      model: {
        primary: "ollama/llama3.3",
        fallback: ["ollama/qwen2.5-coder:32b"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Fallback Model with CLI Backend in OpenClaw

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/cli-backends.md

Sets up a primary model and a CLI-based model as a fallback in OpenClaw. If the primary model fails (e.g., due to API issues), OpenClaw will automatically attempt to use the specified CLI model.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      model: {
        primary: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5",
        fallbacks: [
          "claude-cli/opus-4.5"
        ]
      },
      models: {
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { alias: "Opus" },
        "claude-cli/opus-4.5": {}
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### OpenClaw Models Aliases and Fallbacks Commands (Bash)

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/cli/models.md

Commands for managing model aliases and fallbacks within OpenClaw. These commands allow users to list existing aliases and fallbacks.

```bash
openclaw models aliases list
openclaw models fallbacks list
```

--------------------------------

### Configure MiniMax M2.1 as Fallback in OpenClaw

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/providers/minimax.md

This JSON configuration sets up MiniMax M2.1 as a fallback model in OpenClaw, with 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-5' as the primary model. This ensures that if the primary model is unavailable, requests will be routed to MiniMax M2.1. It defines aliases for both models.

```json5
{
  env: { MINIMAX_API_KEY: "sk-..." },
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      models: {
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { alias: "opus" },
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.1": { alias: "minimax" }
      },
      model: {
        primary: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5",
        fallbacks: ["minimax/MiniMax-M2.1"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Hybrid LM Studio Configuration with Hosted Fallbacks

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/local-models.md

This configuration prioritizes a hosted model (e.g., Anthropic Sonnet) as primary, with local MiniMax M2.1 and hosted Opus as fallbacks. It uses `models.mode: "merge"` to ensure hosted models remain available when the local setup is unavailable. This provides a balance between local performance and cloud reliability.

```json5
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5",
        "fallbacks": ["lmstudio/minimax-m2.1-gs32", "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5"]
      },
      "models": {
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5": { "alias": "Sonnet" },
        "lmstudio/minimax-m2.1-gs32": { "alias": "MiniMax Local" },
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { "alias": "Opus" }
      }
    }
  },
  "models": {
    "mode": "merge",
    "providers": {
      "lmstudio": {
        "baseUrl": "http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1",
        "apiKey": "lmstudio",
        "api": "openai-responses",
        "models": [
          {
            "id": "minimax-m2.1-gs32",
            "name": "MiniMax M2.1 GS32",
            "reasoning": false,
            "input": ["text"],
            "cost": { "input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0 },
            "contextWindow": 196608,
            "maxTokens": 8192
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Default Agent Model (JSON)

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/platforms/raspberry-pi.md

Sets the default primary and fallback AI models for OpenClaw agents. This JSON configuration specifies 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514' as the primary model and 'openai/gpt-4o-mini' as a fallback.

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
        "fallbacks": ["openai/gpt-4o-mini"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure OpenClaw Agent to Use Ollama Model

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/providers/ollama.md

Specifies the primary and fallback models for OpenClaw agents, directing them to use models hosted by Ollama. The model ID should follow the format 'ollama/<model_name>'.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      model: { primary: "ollama/llama3.3" }
    }
  }
}
```

