### OpenClaw Models Status

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/cli/models.md

Displays the resolved default model, fallbacks, and an authentication overview for configured providers. Includes options for live probing of authentication profiles.

```APIDOC
## GET /openclaw/models/status

### Description
Shows the resolved default model, fallbacks, and an authentication overview. Optionally runs live probes against configured provider profiles.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/openclaw/models/status

### Query Parameters
- **--json** (boolean) - Output in JSON format.
- **--plain** (boolean) - Output in plain text format.
- **--check** (boolean) - Exit with status 1 if auth is expired/missing, 2 if expiring.
- **--probe** (boolean) - Run live authentication probes against each configured provider profile.
- **--probe-provider** (string) - Probe authentication for a specific provider by name.
- **--probe-profile** (string) - Probe specific authentication profile IDs (can be comma-separated).
- **--probe-timeout** (integer) - Set the timeout in milliseconds for authentication probes.
- **--probe-concurrency** (integer) - Set the concurrency level for authentication probes.
- **--probe-max-tokens** (integer) - Set the maximum number of tokens to use for authentication probes.

### Request Example
```bash
openclaw models status --probe --probe-provider openai
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **default_model** (string) - The currently resolved default model.
- **fallbacks** (array) - A list of fallback models.
- **auth_overview** (object) - An overview of authentication status for providers.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "default_model": "openai/gpt-4o",
  "fallbacks": [
    "anthropic/claude-3-opus"
  ],
  "auth_overview": {
    "openai": {
      "status": "valid",
      "expires_in": "2024-12-31"
    },
    "anthropic": {
      "status": "expired"
    }
  }
}
```
```

