### Manage Model Configurations and Aliases

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/cli/index.md

Commands for managing AI models within Openclaw. This includes listing, setting, and managing aliases and fallbacks for models, as well as scanning for available models. Options like `--all`, `--local`, `--provider`, `--json`, and `--plain` offer flexible filtering and output formatting.

```bash
# List all models
openclaw models list --all

# Set the primary model
openclaw models set "claude-3-opus-20240229"

# Add a model alias
openclaw models aliases add my-model "claude-3-sonnet-20240229"

# List image fallbacks
openclaw models image-fallbacks list
```

--------------------------------

### Configure CLI Fallback Backends in JSON5

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/configuration.md

This snippet shows how to configure command-line interface (CLI) backends for text-only fallback runs. It details settings for command paths, arguments, output formats, and specific arguments for models, sessions, and system prompts.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      cliBackends: {
        "claude-cli": {
          command: "/opt/homebrew/bin/claude"
        },
        "my-cli": {
          command: "my-cli",
          args: ["--json"],
          output: "json",
          modelArg: "--model",
          sessionArg: "--session",
          sessionMode: "existing",
          systemPromptArg: "--system",
          systemPromptWhen: "first",
          imageArg: "--image",
          imageMode: "repeat"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

